@title The ConfirmedOwner contract
 @notice A contract with helpers for basic contract ownership.
@notice Allows an owner to begin transferring ownership to a new address.
@notice Allows an ownership transfer to be completed by the recipient.
@notice Get the current owner
@notice validate, transfer ownership, and emit relevant events
@notice validate access
@notice Reverts if called by anyone other than the contract owner.
@param _vrfV2PlusWrapper is the address of the VRFV2Wrapper contract
@notice getBalance returns the native balance of the consumer contract
@notice getLinkToken returns the link token contract

@return the request ID of the most recent VRF V2 request made by this wrapper. This should only
 be relied option within the same transaction that the request was made.

Rather than creatingand funding a VRF V2+ subscription, a user can use this wrapper to create one off requests,paying up front rather than at fulfillment.Since the price is determined using the gas price of the request transaction rather thanthe fulfillment transaction, the wrapper charges an additional premium on callback gasusage, in addition to some extra overhead costs associated with the VRFV2Wrapper contract. *****************************************************************************USAGECalling contracts must inherit from VRFV2PlusWrapperConsumerBase. The consumer must be fundedwith enough LINK or ether to make the request, otherwise requests will revert. To request randomness,call the 'requestRandomWords' function with the desired VRF parameters.
